<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-06T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-06T21:00:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13074: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-07T10:00:00+08:00">May 7, 1935—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 7—2:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>186. Reference Legation’s 184, May 5, 10 a.m.<note n="97" xml:id="d674fn97">Not printed.</note> Following telegram has been
                            received from the Vice Consul at Yunnanfu: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“May 6, 3 p.m. Reds crossing the Yangtze north of Mou, foreigners
                                    returning Yunnanfu.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>